                            <comment id="17046518" author="beobal" created="Thu, 27 Feb 2020 11:23:42 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;A replica will attempt to read a fixed amount of repaired data,&#160;based on the query&apos;s DataLimit, while generating the repaired&#160;digest. If less than that amount is read in the course of satisfying&#160;the query limits, we overread. If more that the amount is read&#160;during the main read phase (because of unrepaired deletions&#160;shadowing repaired data), the digest calculation stops when its&#160;own limit is reached.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/cassandra/compare/trunk...beobal:15601-trunk&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;branch&lt;/a&gt;, &lt;a href=&quot;https://circleci.com/workflow-run/96751ea6-7d08-40dd-839c-e409ffebdb81&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;tests&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
